  "prompt": "How do I submit feedback to Quora?",
  "response": "There are a few ways to submit feedback to Quora:\n\n**1. Through the Quora Website/App (Most Common and Recommended):**\n\n*   **Find the \"Feedback\" or \"Report\" option:** Look for a small \"Feedback\" or \"Report\" link, often found in the following places:\n    *   **On specific content:** Under individual questions, answers, comments, or posts. It's usually a small three-dot menu (...) or a down arrow.\n    *   **In your profile settings:** Click on your profile picture or name, then go to \"Settings\" or \"Privacy\".  You might find a \"Feedback\" or \"Help\" section there.\n    *   **At the bottom of the page:** Scroll to the very bottom of a Quora page. There might be a \"Feedback\" or \"About\" link in the footer.\n\n*   **Fill out the form:** When you click on \"Feedback\" or \"Report,\" a form will usually pop up.\n    *   **Choose the appropriate category:**  Select the type of feedback you are giving (e.g., bug report, suggestion, content violation, account issue, etc.).\n    *   **Provide details:**  Be as specific as possible.  Explain the problem or suggestion clearly.  Include links to the specific question, answer, or user if relevant.  The more information you give, the easier it is for Quora to understand and address your feedback.\n    *   **Screenshots:** If possible, include a screenshot of the issue. This is extremely helpful for bug reports.\n    *   **Submit:** Click the \"Submit\" or \"Send\" button.\n\n**2. Through Quora Support/Help Center (If you can find it):**\n\n*   Quora used to have a more readily accessible \"Help Center,\" but it's become less prominent.  You may be able to find a link to it through your settings or by searching on Quora itself for \"Quora Help\" or \"Quora Support.\"\n*   If you find the Help Center, look for a \"Contact Us\" option or a way to submit a support ticket.\n\n**3. Through the Quora Partner Program (if applicable):**\n\n*   If you are a member of the Quora Partner Program, you may have access to a more direct channel for feedback and support. Look for contact information or feedback mechanisms within the Partner Program dashboard.\n\n**4. Through Social Media (Less Likely to Get a Direct Response):**\n\n*   You *could* try contacting Quora through their social media channels (e.g., Twitter), but this is generally not the most effective way to get a response to specific issues. It's better for general comments or observations.\n\n**Important Tips for Effective Feedback:**\n\n*   **Be clear and concise:** Get straight to the point.\n*   **Be specific:** Include details, examples, and links.\n*   **Be polite and respectful:** Even if you're frustrated, a calm and polite tone will be more effective.\n*   **Focus on one issue at a time:** Submit separate feedback forms for different issues.\n*   **Don't expect an immediate response:** Quora receives a lot of feedback, and they may not be able to respond to every submission individually.\n\nBy following these steps, you'll increase the chances of your feedback being heard and addressed by Quora. Good luck!\n",
